// OmniScript Document Template
// A basic document structure for reports, articles, and written content

@meta {
  title: "Document Title";
  author: "Author Name";
  date: "2026-01-22";
  version: "1.0";
}

@doc {
  # Introduction

  Welcome to this document. This template provides a starting structure
  for creating written content like reports, articles, and documentation.

  ## Purpose

  Describe the purpose of this document here. What will readers learn
  or accomplish by reading this?
}

@doc {
  # Main Content

  This is where your main content goes. You can use **bold** and *italic*
  formatting, as well as:

  - Bullet lists
  - For quick points
  - And easy reading

  Or numbered lists:

  1. First step or point
  2. Second step or point
  3. Third step or point

  ### Subsections

  Break your content into logical subsections using headings.

  > You can also use blockquotes for important callouts or citations.
}

@doc {
  # Conclusion

  Summarize the key points and provide any next steps or
  recommendations for the reader.

  ## References

  - [Reference 1](https://example.com)
  - [Reference 2](https://example.com)
}
